CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published (backwards) in Flash Newspicture Magazine, December 13, 1937, pg. 26, reads: "On the Social Welfare and Labor Front in Pittsburgh, Pa., are Henry G. Parker, Jr., Executive Secretary of the Y. M. C. A., and William Berry, a member of the Urban League staff. They are pictured in Mr. Berry's office during an informal chat."
TitMainTitle: William Berry seated at his desk, with Henry G. Parker standing beside him, possibly in Urban League offices
